Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana. GCIS CAPE TOWN - The budget speech will not be delayed and will still happen in the Parliamentary precinct. The budget is usually tabled in the National Assembly, but since the chamber has been gutted, alternative plans have been put in place. READ: Parliament considering alternative venues for SONA, budget Finance minister Enoch Godongwana will deliver the budget speech at Good Hope Chamber. This is the first time in history the budget is not being tabled in the National Assembly. READ: Parliament Fire | Sona, Budget Speech to go ahead Parliament's presiding officers and chief whips of political parties have endorsed the decision. The Good Hope Chamber was historically used for sittings of the Cape Legislative Assembly between 1854 and 1885 and is one of Parliament's oldest meeting rooms.